title: My Australia
author: milly
text: hear the foamy waves roll gently in ,  while delighted squeals come from within.  kookaburras chuckle in a golden light,  children laughing,  faces bright.   see rippled sands carved of turquoise seas,   then the eucalyptus in an ocean breeze .  grey brown shrubs parched in summer heat,  the sea a million diamonds jiving to the beat.   taste the fluffy lamingtons chocolaty and sweet pavlova and  vegemite,  an essential aussie treat.  tim tams and anzacs,  as all aussies know,   are melt in your mouth favourites as good as food can go.   feel crisp turquoise waters lapping at my feet,  sparkling sapphires dancing to a watery beat.  an everlasting sun beating on my face,  silvery sand in my toes really is an ace.    smell the rich red soil after a summer storm,  the meaty aroma of sausages off the grill,  still warm.  salty sea air drifting in a breeze,  treats from a bonfire,  now if you please!
